00:15:00.357 --> 00:15:03.357
Just give me the suit. let me
finish this once and for all.

255
00:15:03.438 --> 00:15:04.438
No.

256
00:15:04.638 --> 00:15:06.438
I have Cross's complete trust.

257
00:15:06.462 --> 00:15:07.229
It's too dangerous.

258
00:15:07.325 --> 00:15:08.858
We don't have a choice.

259
00:15:09.055 --> 00:15:11.122
Well. that's not entirely true.

260
00:15:12.851 --> 00:15:14.518
I think I found a guy.

261
00:15:16.496 --> 00:15:17.496
Who?

262
00:15:22.219 --> 00:15:23.219
Daddy!

263
00:15:23.644 --> 00:15:24.644
Peanut!

264
00:15:24.722 --> 00:15:26.222
Oh! Happy birthday!

265
00:15:27.987 --> 00:15:30.220
I'm so sorry I'm late. I didn't know
what time your party started.

266
00:15:30.312 --> 00:15:31.979
It was on the invitation!

267
00:15:32.078 --> 00:15:33.945
He didn't get an invitation!

268
00:15:34.003 --> 00:15:35.270
But he came anyway.

269
00:15:35.641 --> 00:15:38.407
Well. I'm not going to miss my
little girl's birthday party.

270
00:15:38.553 --> 00:15:40.953
- I'm gonna go tell mommy you're here.
- Oh. you don't...

271
00:15:41.070 --> 00:15:42.070
What are you doing here. Lang?

272
00:15:42.470 --> 00:15:44.002
You haven't paid a dime in child support.

273
00:15:44.050 --> 00:15:45.383
You know. right now if I wanted to.
I could arrest you.

274
00:15:45.456 --> 00:15:47.023
Good to see you too. Paxton.

275
00:15:47.037 --> 00:15:51.237
Mommy's so happy you're here.
she choked on her drink.  Ha ha.

276
00:15:51.742 --> 00:15:53.742
Hey. look what I have for you.

277
00:15:53.895 --> 00:15:55.095
Can I open it now?

278
00:15:55.892 --> 00:15:58.625
Of course sweetheart. it's your birthday.

279
00:16:01.650 --> 00:16:03.616
You're my bestest friend!

280
00:16:03.796 --> 00:16:05.063
What is that thing?

281
00:16:05.147 --> 00:16:06.447
He's so ugly!

282
00:16:06.953 --> 00:16:08.352
I love him!

283
00:16:09.194 --> 00:16:10.861
Can I go show my friends?

284
00:16:11.173 --> 00:16:12.340
Yeah. of course sweetheart. go ahead.

285
00:16:13.367 --> 00:16:15.034
You're my bestest friend!

286
00:16:15.325 --> 00:16:17.192
Look. the child support is coming.

287
00:16:17.196 --> 00:16:19.263
All right. it's just hard finding a job
when you have a record.

288
00:16:19.330 --> 00:16:21.763
I'm sure you'll figure it out. but y'know.
I want you out of my house.

289
00:16:21.831 --> 00:16:24.298
- No. wait. it's my daughter's birthday!
- It's my house!

290
00:16:24.312 --> 00:16:25.845
- So what. it's my kid!
- Relax!

291
00:16:26.562 --> 00:16:27.629
You can't just show up here.

292
00:16:27.634 --> 00:16:29.034
You know that. c'mon.

293
00:16:29.038 --> 00:16:30.005
It's a birthday party.

294
00:16:30.060 --> 00:16:31.992
Yeah. I know. but you
can't just show up.

295
00:16:32.032 --> 00:16:34.399
- She's my daughter.
- You don't know the first thing about being a father.

296
00:16:34.424 --> 00:16:38.657
Maggie. I tell you this as a friend.
and as the first love of my life.

297
00:16:38.694 --> 00:16:40.427
your fiance is an ass-hat.

298
00:16:40.617 --> 00:16:41.350
He's not an ass-hat.

299
00:16:41.353 --> 00:16:42.853
Hey. watch your language. okay!

300
00:16:42.926 --> 00:16:44.993
Oh. what language.
I said hat.

301
00:16:47.423 --> 00:16:49.157
Really. Maggie?
That guy?

302
00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:52.647
Come on. you could marry anyone you want.
you have to get engaged to a cop?

303
00:16:52.721 --> 00:16:54.454
At least he's not a crook.

304
00:16:55.680 --> 00:16:58.013
I'm trying. okay?  I've changed. uh...

305
00:16:58.021 --> 00:17:00.221
I'm straight. I had a job. and...

306
00:17:02.703 --> 00:17:06.403
I want to provide.  I've had a lot of time
to think about it. and I love her.

307
00:17:06.493 --> 00:17:11.193
So much.  I've missed so much time and
I want to be a part of her life.

308
00:17:11.200 --> 00:17:12.200
What do I do?

309
00:17:12.433 --> 00:17:13.766
Get an apartment.

310
00:17:14.237 --> 00:17:16.837
Get a job. pay child support.

311
00:17:17.243 --> 00:17:20.242
And then we will talk about
visitation. I promise.

312
00:17:20.631 --> 00:17:22.164
You're her hero. Scott.

313
00:17:23.562 --> 00:17:27.095
Just. be the person that she
already thinks you are.

314
00:17:40.980 --> 00:17:42.479
(musical horn)

315
00:17:51.742 --> 00:17:55.342
I'm sorry you have such deep concerns
about the Yellowjacket. Frank.

316
00:17:55.366 --> 00:17:58.233
Yeah. well uh. unfortunately

317
00:17:58.946 --> 00:18:01.213
we can't just do whatever we want.

318
00:18:02.544 --> 00:18:04.411
Would be nice though. right?
Heh heh heh.

319
00:18:05.567 --> 00:18:06.733
But there are laws.

320
00:18:06.746 --> 00:18:07.746
What laws? Of man?

321
00:18:09.059 --> 00:18:11.259
The laws of nature transcend
the laws of man.

322
00:18:11.353 --> 00:18:14.020
And I've transcended
the laws of nature.

323
00:18:16.326 --> 00:18:18.926
Darren. I don't think you understand-

324
00:18:26.354 --> 00:18:29.087
We still haven't worked out all the bugs.

325
00:18:33.759 --> 00:18:34.759
Goodbye Frank.

326
00:18:54.281 --> 00:18:56.681
You know I've been thinking a lot
about gratitude lately

327
00:18:56.699 --> 00:19:00.999
and today during my morning meditation. an
interesting thought occurred to me and

328
00:19:01.034 --> 00:19:02.601
I think it might apply to you too.

329
00:19:02.628 --> 00:19:03.528
How's that?

330
00:19:03.539 --> 00:19:05.472
Gratitude can be forgiveness.

331
00:19:06.662 --> 00:19:10.195
I spent years carrying around my
anger for Hank Pym.

332
00:19:10.572 --> 00:19:12.372
I devoted my genius to him.

333
00:19:13.456 --> 00:19:15.256
I could've worked anywhere.

334
00:19:15.818 --> 00:19:17.483
I chose my mentor poorly.

335
00:19:18.274 --> 00:19:20.274
You didn't even have a choice.

336
00:19:20.626 --> 00:19:22.293
He never believed in you.

337
00:19:23.722 --> 00:19:28.388
It's a shame what we had to do.
but he forced us to do it. didn't he?

338
00:19:29.113 --> 00:19:32.446
But we shouldn't be angry.
we should be grateful.

339
00:19:32.778 --> 00:19:34.978
Because his failures as a mentor.

340
00:19:35.649 --> 00:19:36.649
as a father.

341
00:19:38.350 --> 00:19:40.350
forced us to spread our wings.

342
00:19:44.334 --> 00:19:46.000
You're a success. Darren.

343
00:19:47.143 --> 00:19:49.743
You deserve everything coming your way.

344
00:20:09.710 --> 00:20:10.510
Ooh!

345
00:20:11.045 --> 00:20:12.045
Stop cheating.

346
00:20:13.161 --> 00:20:14.627
Hey what's up hotshot?

347
00:20:16.518 --> 00:20:17.518
Maybe he didn't hear you.

348
00:20:18.147 --> 00:20:19.347
How was the party?

349
00:20:25.741 --> 00:20:27.274
Tell me about that tip.

350
00:20:27.346 --> 00:20:28.345
Wha?

351
00:20:28.599 --> 00:20:30.466
I wanna know about that tip.

352
00:20:30.755 --> 00:20:32.222
- Oh baby. it's on!
- Hot dog!

353
00:20:32.275 --> 00:20:33.075
It's so on right now!

354
00:20:33.120 --> 00:20:35.553
Calm down. all right. I just need
to know where it came from.

355
00:20:35.615 --> 00:20:37.148
it's gotta be airtight.

356
00:20:37.945 --> 00:20:38.945
Okay.

357
00:20:39.050 --> 00:20:41.417
I was at a wine tasting with my cousin Ernesto

358
00:20:41.420 --> 00:20:43.753
it was mainly reds. and you know
I don't love reds man. y'know. but

359
00:20:43.791 --> 00:20:45.724
there was a rosé that saved the
day. it was delightful.

360
00:20:45.823 --> 00:20:48.723
And. he tells me about this girl
Emily that we used to kick it with.

361
00:20:48.744 --> 00:20:50.711
it was actually the first pair of
boobs that I ever touched.

362
00:20:50.801 --> 00:20:54.333
It's the wrong details.  It's wro-
Has nothing to do with the story.

363
00:20:54.416 --> 00:20:55.416
Go.

364
00:20:55.678 --> 00:20:57.778
So. uh.  He tells me that:

365
00:20:57.830 --> 00:20:58.830
She's working as a housekeeper now. right?

366
00:20:59.755 --> 00:21:03.355
And she's dating this dude Carlos who's
a shot caller from across the bay and

367
00:21:03.366 --> 00:21:06.566
she tells him about the dude that
she's cleaning for. Right?

368
00:21:06.602 --> 00:21:10.769
That he's. like. this big-shot CEO that
is all retired now but he's loaded.

369
00:21:10.860 --> 00:21:14.560
And so. Carlos and Ernesto are
on the same softball team

370
00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:16.549
and the get to talking. right.

371
00:21:16.607 --> 00:21:17.574
And here comes the good part.

372
00:21:17.638 --> 00:21:18.638
Carlos says:

373
00:21:18.724 --> 00:21:23.024
Yo. man. This guy's got a big-ass safe
just sitting in the basement.

374
00:21:23.037 --> 00:21:24.037
Just chillin'.

375
00:21:24.067 --> 00:21:26.200
Of course Ernesto comes to me 'cause
he knows I've got mad thieving skills.

376
00:21:26.293 --> 00:21:27.260
Of course I ask him:

377
00:21:27.263 --> 00:21:30.763
Did Emily tell Carlos to tell you
to get to me what kind of safe it was?

378
00:21:30.851 --> 00:21:31.551
And he says

379
00:21:31.563 --> 00:21:34.663
Naw. dog. All she said is that
it's. like. super legit. and

380
00:21:34.892 --> 00:21:37.225
whatever's in it has gotta be good!

381
00:21:40.020 --> 00:21:41.020
What?

382
00:21:41.305 --> 00:21:43.105
Old man have safe.

383
00:21:44.206 --> 00:21:45.573
And he's gone for a week.

384
00:21:45.627 --> 00:21:48.727
All right.  There's an old man. he's got
a safe. and he's gone for a week.

385
00:21:48.794 --> 00:21:50.327
Let's just work with that.

386
00:21:50.372 --> 00:21:51.505
Y'know what I' sayin'.

387
00:22:40.885 --> 00:22:43.219
Landlines cut. cell signals jammed.

388
00:22:43.328 --> 00:22:45.928
No one will be making
for distress call tonight.

389
00:22:45.975 --> 00:22:46.975
All check.

390
00:22:47.045 --> 00:22:48.245
- Check.
- Check.

391
00:22:48.643 --> 00:22:50.643
If the job goes bad. you know
I got your back. right?

392
00:22:50.660 --> 00:22:52.992
Don't worry. it's not gonna happen.

393
00:22:56.703 --> 00:22:57.736
I love it when he gets cocky.

394
00:23:04.296 --> 00:23:05.296
Damn!

395
00:23:33.086 --> 00:23:34.086
Alarm is dead.

396
00:23:34.509 --> 00:23:35.509
Nice!

397
00:23:37.701 --> 00:23:40.367
All right. I'm moving through the house.

398
00:24:05.052 --> 00:24:06.952
There's a fingerprint lock on the door.

399
00:24:07.036 --> 00:24:08.003
He's got a what?

400
00:24:08.064 --> 00:24:09.964
Ernesto didn't tell me nothing about that.

401
00:24:09.975 --> 00:24:11.575
Aw. man. are we screwed?

402
00:24:11.826 --> 00:24:12.893
Not necessarily.

403
00:25:01.943 --> 00:25:02.943
I'm in.

404
00:25:02.995 --> 00:25:05.562
No alarms have been triggered.
He's in like the Flynn.

405
00:25:10.230 --> 00:25:11.630
Oh. man.

406
00:25:11.674 --> 00:25:12.674
What is it?

407
00:25:13.680 --> 00:25:16.447
Well they weren't kidding.
This safe is serious.

408
00:25:16.732 --> 00:25:18.799
How serious we talkin'. Scotty?

409
00:25:18.998 --> 00:25:20.198
It's a Carbondale.

410
00:25:20.600 --> 00:25:21.600
It's from 1910.

411
00:25:21.990 --> 00:25:24.723
Made from the same steel
as the Titanic.

412
00:25:25.070 --> 00:25:26.070
Wow.

413
00:25:26.119 --> 00:25:27.252
Can you crack it?

414
00:25:27.605 --> 00:25:28.838
Well. here's the thing.

415
00:25:28.929 --> 00:25:31.196
It doesn't do so well in the cold.

416
00:25:31.303 --> 00:25:32.670
Remember what that iceberg did?

417
00:25:32.769 --> 00:25:34.269
Yeah. man. it killed DiCaprio.

418
00:25:34.278 --> 00:25:35.411
Killed everybody.

419
00:25:35.489 --> 00:25:36.789
Man. not kill the old lady.

420
00:25:36.855 --> 00:25:39.655
She still throw the jewel into the oceans.

421
00:26:31.693 --> 00:26:32.693
What're you doing?

422
00:26:32.772 --> 00:26:35.572
I poured water in the locking mechanism
and froze it with nitrogen.

423
00:26:36.216 --> 00:26:38.016
Ice expands. metal doesn't.

424
00:26:39.339 --> 00:26:40.272
What are you doing now?

425
00:26:40.334 --> 00:26:41.334
Waiting.

426
00:26:42.469 --> 00:26:43.469
Waiting.

427
00:26:51.799 --> 00:26:52.799
Nice.

428
00:26:57.093 --> 00:26:58.759
What is it. cash? Jewels?

429
00:27:00.253 --> 00:27:01.353
There's nothing here.

430
00:27:01.422 --> 00:27:02.422
What'd you say?

431
00:27:03.223 --> 00:27:04.523
It's a suit.

432
00:27:04.541 --> 00:27:05.541
What?

433
00:27:05.920 --> 00:27:08.087
It's an old motorcycle suit.

434
00:27:08.913 --> 00:27:10.780
There's no cash. no jewelry. nothing?

435
00:27:10.807 --> 00:27:11.806
No.

436
00:27:13.236 --> 00:27:14.236
It's a bust.

437
00:27:14.684 --> 00:27:16.351
I'm really sorry. Scotty.

438
00:27:17.054 --> 00:27:18.854
I know you needed a score.

439
00:27:53.310 --> 00:27:55.243
I thought we were using mice?

440
00:27:55.543 --> 00:27:57.009
What's the difference?

441
00:27:58.389 --> 00:28:00.055
Commence experiment 34-C.

442
00:28:01.448 --> 00:28:03.115
organic atomic reduction.

443
00:28:03.726 --> 00:28:04.826
Darren. maybe we should think-

444
00:28:04.906 --> 00:28:07.406
Shrinking organic tissue is the
centerpiece of this technology.

445
00:28:07.431 --> 00:28:10.831
I can't go to the buyers
with half a breakthrough.

446
00:28:34.141 --> 00:28:37.674
Experiment 34-C results...

447
00:28:38.302 --> 00:28:39.302
negative.

448
00:28:43.858 --> 00:28:47.124
Sanitize the workstation.
bring in subject 35-C.

449
00:28:58.312 --> 00:29:00.112
Why would you lock this up?

450
00:29:22.335 --> 00:29:23.335
So weird.

451
00:29:56.028 --> 00:29:57.028
Scott. what's up man?

452
00:30:02.746 --> 00:30:04.346
I wonder...what is this?

453
00:30:35.170 --> 00:30:39.170
The world sure seems different
from down here. doesn't it. Scott?

454
00:30:39.186 --> 00:30:40.786
What? Who...who said that?

455
00:30:45.902 --> 00:30:48.202
Luis! Luis. I'm here!

456
00:30:49.091 --> 00:30:50.958
It's a trial by fire. Scott.

457
00:30:51.808 --> 00:30:52.875
Or in this case.

458
00:30:53.390 --> 00:30:54.390
water.

459
00:31:18.618 --> 00:31:21.151
Guess you're tougher than you thought.

460
00:31:23.758 --> 00:31:25.691
Oh. I don't want to see this.

461
00:31:25.746 --> 00:31:26.746
Luis!

462
00:31:32.013 --> 00:31:33.012
Son of a-!

463
00:32:49.789 --> 00:32:50.789
What the hell?

464
00:32:52.786 --> 00:32:54.452
Not bad for a test drive.

465
00:32:54.776 --> 00:32:56.909
Keep the suit.
I'll be in touch.

466
00:32:57.376 --> 00:32:58.376
No. no. No.

467
00:32:58.427 --> 00:32:59.427
No thank you.

468
00:33:11.883 --> 00:33:13.216
Put it down on the ground!

469
00:33:13.281 --> 00:33:14.581
You are under arrest!

470
00:33:14.593 --> 00:33:15.460
No. I didn't steal anything!

471
00:33:15.547 --> 00:33:17.214
I was returning
something I stole.

472
00:33:26.865 --> 00:33:30.132
You know. you almost had us convinced
that you were going to change your ways.

473
00:33:30.611 --> 00:33:32.810
They were really rooting for you.

474
00:33:35.263 --> 00:33:37.263
It's gonna break their hearts.

475
00:33:39.316 --> 00:33:40.516
You got a visitor.

476
00:33:41.176 --> 00:33:42.176
Who?

477
00:33:42.177 --> 00:33:43.177
Your lawyer.

478
00:33:44.228 --> 00:33:45.228
My lawyer?

479
00:33:48.547 --> 00:33:50.814
I told you I'd be in touch. Scott.

480
00:33:51.730 --> 00:33:56.062
I'm starting to think that you
prefer the inside of a jail cell.

481
00:33:56.323 --> 00:33:57.323
Oh man.

482
00:33:57.618 --> 00:33:58.618
Sit down.

483
00:34:02.852 --> 00:34:04.785
Sir. I'm sorry I stole the suit.

484
00:34:05.414 --> 00:34:07.581
I don't even want to
know why you have it.

485
00:34:07.620 --> 00:34:09.420
Maggie was right about you.

486
00:34:11.143 --> 00:34:12.010
How do you know about-

487
00:34:12.054 --> 00:34:15.454
The way she's trying to keep
you away from Cassie.

488
00:34:15.544 --> 00:34:19.010
The moment things get hard.
you turn right back to crime.

489
00:34:21.359 --> 00:34:23.559
The way I see it. you have a choice.

490
00:34:23.580 --> 00:34:26.213
You can either spend the
rest of your life in prison

491
00:34:26.727 --> 00:34:31.260
or go back to your cell
and await further instructions.

492
00:34:32.138 --> 00:34:33.405
I don't understand.

493
00:34:33.461 --> 00:34:34.928
I don't expect you to.

494
00:34:35.726 --> 00:34:37.526
But you don't have many options right now.

495
00:34:37.619 --> 00:34:39.686
Quite frankly. neither do I.

496
00:34:41.490 --> 00:34:44.989
Why do you think I let you steal
that suit in the first place?

497
00:34:45.044 --> 00:34:46.044
What?

498
00:34:56.444 --> 00:34:59.644
Second chances don't come
around all that much.

499
00:34:59.959 --> 00:35:02.625
So next time you think you might see one

500
00:35:02.860 --> 00:35:06.726
I suggest you take a real close look at it.

501
00:35:19.487 --> 00:35:21.220
You are my bestest friend!

502
00:35:21.397 --> 00:35:23.897
Are you sure you don't
want a different toy?

503
00:35:23.920 --> 00:35:25.253
No. I love this one.

504
00:35:26.197 --> 00:35:27.197
Okay.

505
00:35:27.463 --> 00:35:29.197
Well. get some sleep then.

506
00:35:29.583 --> 00:35:30.582
- Mommy.
- Hm?

507
00:35:31.204 --> 00:35:32.471
Is daddy a bad man?

508
00:35:33.469 --> 00:35:35.869
I heard some grown ups say he's bad.

509
00:35:37.737 --> 00:35:38.737
No.

510
00:35:39.681 --> 00:35:42.748
Daddy just gets confused
sometimes. you know?

511
00:36:34.173 --> 00:36:36.573
Smart choice.
You actually listened for once.

512
00:36:38.386 --> 00:36:39.386
Under the door.

513
00:36:44.398 --> 00:36:45.665
Okay. Where to now?

514
00:36:45.979 --> 00:36:46.979
Hang tight.

515
00:36:50.735 --> 00:36:51.735
What? What?!

516
00:36:51.972 --> 00:36:52.939
Where the hell did he go?

517
00:36:52.941 --> 00:36:54.408
I have no idea. he just vanished.

518
00:36:54.459 --> 00:36:56.092
Set up a five block perimeter. now!

519
00:36:56.170 --> 00:36:57.803
Get back. get back. get back!

520
00:36:57.843 --> 00:36:59.710
Scott. These are my associates.

521
00:36:59.801 --> 00:37:01.934
Huh? You got a camera on an ant?

522
00:37:02.689 --> 00:37:04.022
Yeah. sure. why not?

523
00:37:04.300 --> 00:37:05.266
Where's the car?

524
00:37:05.331 --> 00:37:06.831
No car. we've got wings.

525
00:37:06.892 --> 00:37:07.892
Incoming!

526
00:37:18.490 --> 00:37:21.090
Put your foot on the
central node and not the thorax.

527
00:37:21.171 --> 00:37:22.304
Are you ki- How safe's Th-

528
00:37:22.392 --> 00:37:24.192
Get on the damn ant. Scott.

529
00:37:36.337 --> 00:37:37.603
Why am I on a police car?

530
00:37:37.666 --> 00:37:39.799
Shouldn't I not be on a police car?

531
00:37:39.838 --> 00:37:42.805
So they can give you a lift
past their five block perimeter.

532
00:37:42.814 --> 00:37:43.581
Whoa. All right.

533
00:37:43.726 --> 00:37:45.159
Now. what's the next move?

534
00:37:45.212 --> 00:37:46.112
Hang on tight.

535
00:37:46.177 --> 00:37:47.910
Oh. this is easy.
I'm getting the hang of this.

536
00:37:47.947 --> 00:37:48.947
Yank up to go up.
It's like a horse.

537
00:37:49.916 --> 00:37:51.749
You're throwing 247 off balance.

538
00:37:51.848 --> 00:37:54.247
- Wait. his name is 247?
- He doesn't have a name.

539
00:37:54.248 --> 00:37:55.415
he has a number Scott. do you have

540
00:37:55.510 --> 00:37:57.710
any idea how many ants there are?

541
00:37:58.530 --> 00:37:59.530
Whoa!

542
00:37:59.940 --> 00:38:01.240
Please...maybe it's 248?

543
00:38:01.240 --> 00:38:02.773
No no no no no
vertigo. vertigo!

544
00:38:02.949 --> 00:38:03.949
No. I think it's 247.

545
00:38:05.282 --> 00:38:06.482
- Wait.
- Hang on.

546
00:38:07.427 --> 00:38:08.427
I think I'm getting the hang of this.

547
00:38:08.911 --> 00:38:12.178
I'm controlling 247.
He is not listening to you.

548
00:38:12.295 --> 00:38:13.295
What?

549
00:38:13.509 --> 00:38:14.409
Can I make one little request?

550
00:38:14.439 --> 00:38:15.439
No.

551
00:38:16.132 --> 00:38:18.731
Stop New York City. time out. time out.

552
00:38:19.414 --> 00:38:20.414
Time out.

553
00:38:20.688 --> 00:38:21.954
All right. hold on.

554
00:38:22.389 --> 00:38:23.789
Just. wait. whoa. uh!

555
00:38:24.151 --> 00:38:26.218
What happens if I
throw up in this helmet?

556
00:38:26.284 --> 00:38:28.884
It's my helmet Scott.
Do not throw up.

557
00:38:29.376 --> 00:38:30.609
Just set 'er down. all right?

558
00:38:30.664 --> 00:38:32.031
I'm getting light headed.

559
00:38:32.102 --> 00:38:33.102
Hang on. Scott.

560
00:38:33.586 --> 00:38:35.219
Yeah. I'm getting a little light...

561
00:38:35.237 --> 00:38:36.304
-t's. it's funny...

562
00:38:38.335 --> 00:38:39.735
...hit me. andfarness-

563
00:38:59.443 --> 00:39:00.443
Hello.

564
00:39:04.051 --> 00:39:05.051
Who are you?

565
00:39:07.648 --> 00:39:10.114
Have you been standing there
watching me sleep this whole time?

566
00:39:10.144 --> 00:39:11.144
Yes.

567
00:39:11.653 --> 00:39:12.653
Why?

568
00:39:12.927 --> 00:39:16.727
Because the last time you were
here you stole something.

569
00:39:16.885 --> 00:39:18.585
Oh. Oh!

570
00:39:19.004 --> 00:39:20.004
Hey. look.

571
00:39:21.287 --> 00:39:22.287
Whoa!

572
00:39:27.071 --> 00:39:28.337
Paraponera clavata.

573
00:39:28.648 --> 00:39:31.848
Giant tropical bullet ants ranked
highest on the Schmidt pain index.

574
00:39:31.852 --> 00:39:33.819
they're here to keep an eye
on you when I can't.

575
00:39:34.858 --> 00:39:37.325
Dr. Pym's waiting for you downstairs.

576
00:39:38.284 --> 00:39:39.284
Who?

577
00:39:40.407 --> 00:39:42.607
Ahhh...hey. um.

578
00:39:43.399 --> 00:39:44.999
whose pajamas are these?

579
00:39:51.624 --> 00:39:53.657
How am I supposed to do this?

580
00:40:00.301 --> 00:40:02.435
Hey. j- just one step at a time.

581
00:40:05.055 --> 00:40:06.055
Ugh.

582
00:40:07.789 --> 00:40:10.855
You don't bite me.
I don't step on you. deal?

583
00:40:16.202 --> 00:40:18.269
Take down the servers and
Cross wouldn't even know.

584
00:40:18.285 --> 00:40:19.718
We don't need this guy.

585
00:40:19.770 --> 00:40:22.270
I assume that you've already
met my daughter Hope.

586
00:40:22.275 --> 00:40:23.275
I did.

587
00:40:23.464 --> 00:40:24.464
She's great.

588
00:40:24.876 --> 00:40:26.776
She doesn't think that we need you.

589
00:40:26.793 --> 00:40:28.726
We don't. We can do this ourselves.

590
00:40:28.795 --> 00:40:32.662
I go to all this effort to let you
steal my suit. and then Hope

591
00:40:32.710 --> 00:40:33.843
has you arrested.

592
00:40:34.650 --> 00:40:37.583
Okay. we can try this and
when he fails I'll do it myself.

593
00:40:37.668 --> 00:40:41.200
She's a little bit anxious.
It has to do with this job.

594
00:40:41.246 --> 00:40:43.946
which. judging by the fact that
you're sitting opposite me.

595
00:40:43.998 --> 00:40:46.198
I take it that you're interested in.

596
00:40:46.259 --> 00:40:47.159
What job?

597
00:40:47.256 --> 00:40:48.856
Would you like some tea?

598
00:40:49.120 --> 00:40:50.120
Uh. sure.

599
00:40:50.884 --> 00:40:55.284
I was very impressed with how you
managed to get past my security system.

600
00:40:56.357 --> 00:40:58.790
Freezing that metal was particularly clever.

601
00:41:00.018 --> 00:41:01.218
Were you watching me?

602
00:41:01.237 --> 00:41:04.036
Scott. I've been watching you for a while.

603
00:41:04.534 --> 00:41:06.734
ever since you robbed Vista Corp.

604
00:41:08.331 --> 00:41:12.098
Oh. excuse me. burgled Vista Corp.

605
00:41:13.924 --> 00:41:17.424
Vista's security system is one of the most
advanced in the business.

606
00:41:17.478 --> 00:41:20.678
It's supposed to be unbeatable
but you beat it.

607
00:41:21.651 --> 00:41:22.784
Would you like some sugar?

608
00:41:23.139 --> 00:41:24.139
Yeah. thanks.

609
00:41:28.291 --> 00:41:29.891
You know what. I'm okay.

610
00:41:34.878 --> 00:41:36.811
How do you make them do that?

611
00:41:36.847 --> 00:41:39.647
Ants can lift objects
fifty times their weight.

612
00:41:39.690 --> 00:41:42.857
They build. farm. they
cooperate with each other.

613
00:41:43.195 --> 00:41:45.928
Right. But how do you
make them do that?

614
00:41:47.073 --> 00:41:52.838
I use electromagnetic waves. to
stimulate their olfactory nerve center.

615
00:41:54.010 --> 00:41:55.876
I speak to them.

616
00:41:56.168 --> 00:41:59.768
I can go anywhere. hear
anything. and see everything.

617
00:42:00.078 --> 00:42:02.111
And still know absolutely nothing.

618
00:42:02.393 --> 00:42:03.926
I'm late to meet Cross.

619
00:42:07.680 --> 00:42:09.180
Uh...Dr. Pym?

620
00:42:09.505 --> 00:42:12.038
You don't need to raise your hand. Scott.

621
00:42:12.233 --> 00:42:14.365
Sorry. I just have one question.

622
00:42:14.491 --> 00:42:19.057
Who are you who is she what the hell's
going on and can I go back to jail now?

623
00:42:19.209 --> 00:42:20.209
Come with me.

624
00:42:20.901 --> 00:42:24.968
Twenty years ago I created a formula
that altered atomic relative distance.

625
00:42:25.038 --> 00:42:26.038
Huh?

626
00:42:26.399 --> 00:42:30.399
I learned how to change the distance
between atoms. that's what powers the suit.

627
00:42:30.411 --> 00:42:31.744
that's why it works.

628
00:42:33.324 --> 00:42:34.324
Wow!

629
00:42:39.612 --> 00:42:41.245
- Whoa.
- It was dangerous.

630
00:42:41.981 --> 00:42:43.381
It was too dangerous.

631
00:42:45.163 --> 00:42:47.263
So I hid it from the world.

632
00:42:47.648 --> 00:42:51.848
And that's when I switched gears
and I started my own company.

633
00:42:51.881 --> 00:42:52.881
Pym Tech.

634
00:42:53.179 --> 00:42:54.179
Yes.

635
00:42:55.416 --> 00:42:58.549
I took on a young protege
called Darren Cross.

636
00:42:58.853 --> 00:43:00.920
Darren Cross.
He's a big deal.

637
00:43:01.609 --> 00:43:04.242
But before he was a big deal
he was my assistant.

638
00:43:04.307 --> 00:43:08.374
I thought I saw something in him.
a son I never had perhaps.

639
00:43:08.561 --> 00:43:11.828
He was brilliant. but as we became
close he began to suspect

640
00:43:11.903 --> 00:43:14.370
that I wasn't telling him everything.

641
00:43:14.371 --> 00:43:18.171
He heard rumors about what
was called the Pym Particles.

642
00:43:18.636 --> 00:43:21.769
and he became obsessed with
recreating my formula.

643
00:43:22.059 --> 00:43:24.625
But I wouldn't help him so he
conspired against me and

644
00:43:24.708 --> 00:43:26.974
he voted me out of my own company.

645
00:43:27.180 --> 00:43:28.580
How could he do that?

646
00:43:28.764 --> 00:43:31.630
The board's chairman
is my daughter. Hope.

647
00:43:31.652 --> 00:43:33.385
She was the deciding vote.

648
00:43:34.502 --> 00:43:39.502
But she came back to me when she saw
how close Cross was to cracking my formula.

649
00:43:40.803 --> 00:43:42.803
The process is highly volatile.

650
00:43:43.223 --> 00:43:46.156
What isn't protected by a specialized helmet

651
00:43:46.225 --> 00:43:48.425
can affect the brain's chemistry.

652
00:43:49.139 --> 00:43:55.172
I don't think Darren realizes this. and y'know.
he's not the most stable guy to begin with.

653
00:43:55.238 --> 00:43:57.172
So. what do you want from me?

654
00:43:59.669 --> 00:44:03.802
Scott. I believe that everyone
deserves a shot at redemption.

655
00:44:03.857 --> 00:44:04.857
Do you?

656
00:44:05.190 --> 00:44:06.190
I do.

657
00:44:06.819 --> 00:44:11.752
If you can help me. I promise I can
help you be with your daughter again.

658
00:44:13.265 --> 00:44:15.732
Now are you ready to redeem yourself?

659
00:44:15.786 --> 00:44:16.786
Absolutely.

660
00:44:17.197 --> 00:44:21.197
My days of breaking into places
and stealing shit are done.

661
00:44:22.109 --> 00:44:23.842
What do you want me to do?

662
00:44:24.045 --> 00:44:27.645
I want you to break into a
place and steal some shit.

663
00:44:30.369 --> 00:44:32.136
You going to be home for dinner tonight?

664
00:44:33.176 --> 00:44:35.576
Uh. yeah.
I'll pick something up. okay?

665
00:44:35.589 --> 00:44:36.588
Okay.

666
00:44:36.616 --> 00:44:37.516
Good news?

667
00:44:37.528 --> 00:44:39.461
Uh. I don't know.
It's news.

668
00:44:39.754 --> 00:44:41.887
Are you trying to find my daddy?

669
00:44:44.224 --> 00:44:45.224
Yeah. I am. sweetheart.

670
00:44:46.959 --> 00:44:48.692
I just want your
daddy to be safe.

671
00:44:48.779 --> 00:44:50.446
Hope you don't catch him.

672
00:45:37.267 --> 00:45:39.434
This isn't the first time these guys
have tried to get their hands

673
00:45:39.465 --> 00:45:41.198
on game changing weaponry.

674
00:45:41.882 --> 00:45:45.182
That's Mitchell Carson.
ex-head of defense at SHIELD.

675
00:45:45.266 --> 00:45:48.265
presently in the business
of toppling governments.

676
00:45:48.326 --> 00:45:49.992
He always wanted my tech.

677
00:45:50.293 --> 00:45:53.959
And now. unless we break in
and steal the Yellowjacket

678
00:45:54.048 --> 00:45:55.715
and destroy all the data.

679
00:45:56.886 --> 00:46:00.953
Darren Cross is gonna unleash
chaos upon the world.

680
00:46:03.898 --> 00:46:07.565
I think our first move should
be calling the Avengers.

681
00:46:10.257 --> 00:46:14.956
I've spent half my life trying to keep this
technology out of the hands of a Stark.

682
00:46:15.037 --> 00:46:18.604
I'm sure as hell not going to
hand-deliver it to one now.

683
00:46:18.659 --> 00:46:22.259
This is not some cute technology
like the Iron Man suit.

684
00:46:22.272 --> 00:46:25.005
This could change the texture of reality.

685
00:46:26.890 --> 00:46:31.290
Besides they're probably too busy
dropping cities out of the sky.

686
00:46:31.432 --> 00:46:33.565
Okay. then why don't you just send the ants?

687
00:46:33.655 --> 00:46:35.054
Scott. they are ants.

688
00:46:36.150 --> 00:46:40.483
Ants. they can do a lot of things.
but they still need a leader.

689
00:46:40.767 --> 00:46:45.767
Somebody that can infiltrate a place
that's designed to prevent infiltration.

690
00:46:45.833 --> 00:46:48.633
Hank. I'm a thief.
All right. I'm a good thief.

691
00:46:48.688 --> 00:46:49.388
But this is insane.

692
00:46:49.460 --> 00:46:51.593
He's right Hank and you know it.

693
00:46:51.974 --> 00:46:54.574
You've seen the footage.
you know what Cross is capable of.

694
00:46:54.593 --> 00:46:57.993
I was against using him when we had
months. now we have days.

695
00:46:58.567 --> 00:46:59.967
I'm wearing the suit.

696
00:46:59.967 --> 00:47:00.967
Absolutely not!

697
00:47:01.165 --> 00:47:04.332
I know the facility inside and out.
I know how Cross thinks.

698
00:47:04.380 --> 00:47:05.880
I know this mission better
than anybody here.

699
00:47:05.934 --> 00:47:08.567
We need you close to Cross
otherwise this mission cannot work.

700
00:47:08.615 --> 00:47:11.548
- We don't have time to screw around.
- Hope. please. this is an [?].

701
00:47:11.614 --> 00:47:12.681
He is a criminal.
I'm your daughter.

702
00:47:12.700 --> 00:47:13.700
NO!

703
00:47:52.293 --> 00:47:53.493
She's right. Hank.

704
00:47:54.276 --> 00:47:55.409
I'm not your guy.

705
00:47:56.553 --> 00:47:58.420
Why don't you wear the suit?

706
00:47:58.966 --> 00:48:00.699
You think I don't want to?

707
00:48:01.396 --> 00:48:02.396
I can't.

708
00:48:04.108 --> 00:48:05.775
I spent years wearing it.

709
00:48:06.172 --> 00:48:07.572
It took a toll on me.

710
00:48:16.434 --> 00:48:17.967
You're our only option.

711
00:48:23.242 --> 00:48:27.042
Before Hope lost her mother.
she used to look at me like

712
00:48:27.303 --> 00:48:29.703
I was the greatest man in the world.

713
00:48:31.667 --> 00:48:35.266
And now she looks at me
and it's just disappointment.

714
00:48:38.449 --> 00:48:39.849
It's too late for me.

715
00:48:41.768 --> 00:48:42.835
But not for you.

716
00:48:43.815 --> 00:48:45.149
This is your chance.

717
00:48:45.485 --> 00:48:49.085
The chance to earn that look
in your daughter's eyes.

718
00:48:49.472 --> 00:48:52.938
To become the hero that she
already thinks you are.

719
00:48:53.713 --> 00:48:55.847
It's not about saving our world.

720
00:48:56.868 --> 00:48:58.834
It's about saving theirs.

721
00:49:02.676 --> 00:49:04.609
Damn. that was a good speech.

722
00:49:05.562 --> 00:49:06.562
Scott.

723
00:49:07.384 --> 00:49:10.584
I need you
to be the Ant-Man.

724
00:49:14.770 --> 00:49:18.803
In the right hands. the relationship
between man and suit is symbiotic.

725
00:49:18.955 --> 00:49:22.287
The suit has power. the man
harnesses that power.

726
00:49:22.665 --> 00:49:25.398
You need to be skillful.
agile. and above all.

727
00:49:25.463 --> 00:49:26.796
you need to be fast.

728
00:49:27.061 --> 00:49:30.527
You should be able to shrink
and grow on a dime. so

729
00:49:30.554 --> 00:49:32.821
your size always suits your needs.

730
00:49:35.438 --> 00:49:37.538
Now dive through the keyhole. Scott.

731
00:49:37.578 --> 00:49:39.711
You charge big.
you dive small.

732
00:49:39.868 --> 00:49:41.201
then you emerge big.

733
00:49:44.044 --> 00:49:45.043
Ow!

734
00:49:46.532 --> 00:49:47.532
Ah!

735
00:49:48.417 --> 00:49:49.217
Ow.

736
00:49:49.228 --> 00:49:50.228
Useless.

737
00:49:52.466 --> 00:49:53.799
When you're small energy is compressed

738
00:49:53.834 --> 00:49:55.901
so you have the force of a 200 pound man

739
00:49:55.925 --> 00:49:57.992
behind a fist a 100th of an inch wide

740
00:49:58.035 --> 00:49:59.235
you're like a bullet.

741
00:49:59.298 --> 00:50:00.932
You punch too hard.
you kill someone.

742
00:50:01.014 --> 00:50:02.647
too soft. it's a love-tap.

743
00:50:02.711 --> 00:50:04.278
In other words you have
to know how to punch.

744
00:50:04.321 --> 00:50:06.021
I was in prison for three years.
I know how to punch.

745
00:50:06.101 --> 00:50:07.101
Show me.

746
00:50:07.989 --> 00:50:09.488
- Terrible.
- You want to show me how to punch?

747
00:50:09.722 --> 00:50:10.722
Show me-

748
00:50:12.860 --> 00:50:14.260
That's how you punch.

749
00:50:15.104 --> 00:50:16.837
- She's been looking forward to this.
- No kiddin'.

750
00:50:16.914 --> 00:50:19.914
Hope trained in martial arts
at a. uh. difficult time.

751
00:50:20.195 --> 00:50:22.428
Oh. by difficult time. he
means when my mother died.

752
00:50:22.519 --> 00:50:24.452
We lost her in a plane crash.

753
00:50:24.554 --> 00:50:28.321
It's bad enough you won't tell me how she died.
could you please stop telling me that lie.

754
00:50:28.378 --> 00:50:29.645
We're working here.

755
00:50:32.952 --> 00:50:35.485
All right princess.
let's get back to work.

756
00:50:35.563 --> 00:50:37.430
Were you going for the hand?

757
00:50:43.939 --> 00:50:46.072
You know. I think this regulator
is holding me back.

758
00:50:46.081 --> 00:50:48.214
Do not screw with the regulator.

759
00:50:48.736 --> 00:50:52.303
If that regulator is compromised
you would go sub-atomic.

760
00:50:52.536 --> 00:50:53.869
What does that mean?

761
00:50:54.588 --> 00:50:56.820
It means that you would
enter a quantum realm.

762
00:50:56.918 --> 00:50:57.751
What does that mean?

763
00:50:57.840 --> 00:51:02.873
It means that you would enter a reality
where all concepts of time and space

764
00:51:02.878 --> 00:51:06.711
become irrelevant as you
shrink for all eternity.

765
00:51:08.033 --> 00:51:09.766
Everything that you know.

766
00:51:10.228 --> 00:51:11.761
and love.

767
00:51:12.609 --> 00:51:13.609
gone forever.

768
00:51:15.504 --> 00:51:17.904
Cool. Yeah. I'm-
If it ain't broke.

769
00:51:19.253 --> 00:51:22.918
You've learned about the suit. but you've
yet to learn about your greatest allies

770
00:51:23.886 --> 00:51:24.886
the ants.

771
00:51:25.387 --> 00:51:28.387
Loyal. brave. and
your partners on this job.

772
00:51:34.945 --> 00:51:37.878
Paratrechina longicornis.
commonly known as crazy ants.

773
00:51:37.905 --> 00:51:40.605
they're lightning fast and can conduct
electricity which makes them useful

774
00:51:40.639 --> 00:51:42.572
to fry out enemy electronics.

775
00:51:42.832 --> 00:51:44.364
Oh you're not so crazy.

776
00:51:45.299 --> 00:51:46.433
Hey!  Heh heh heh

777
00:51:47.088 --> 00:51:48.088
You're cute.

778
00:51:49.425 --> 00:51:50.425
Oh! Aaah!

779
00:51:56.435 --> 00:51:58.902
That was a lot scarier
a second ago.

780
00:52:07.006 --> 00:52:08.006
Aaah!

781
00:52:08.360 --> 00:52:11.494
It looks like the Futures lab has
its own isolated power supply.

782
00:52:11.570 --> 00:52:14.103
There's a security guard posted
around the clock. we need you

783
00:52:14.159 --> 00:52:16.926
to take him out to deactivate
the security systems.

784
00:52:16.992 --> 00:52:17.992
Okay.

785
00:52:18.060 --> 00:52:19.060
Who's next?

786
00:52:21.232 --> 00:52:22.432
Paraponera clavata.

787
00:52:22.508 --> 00:52:23.908
I know. Bullet ants. right?

788
00:52:23.975 --> 00:52:25.975
Number one on the Schmidt pain index.

789
00:52:26.071 --> 00:52:26.871
Hey guys!

790
00:52:26.905 --> 00:52:28.838
Remember me from the bedroom?

791
00:52:28.903 --> 00:52:29.703
Whoa!

792
00:52:30.283 --> 00:52:32.049
The Yellowjacket pod is hermetically sealed

793
00:52:32.144 --> 00:52:36.844
and the only access point is a tube
we estimate to be about 5 millimeters in diameter.

794
00:52:36.892 --> 00:52:38.559
Why do I have a sick feeling in my stomach?

795
00:52:38.596 --> 00:52:41.263
The tube is protected by a laser grid
and we can only power that down

796
00:52:41.301 --> 00:52:42.634
for fifteen seconds.

797
00:52:42.719 --> 00:52:47.053
You're going to need to signal the crazy ants
to blow the servers. retrieve the suit.

798
00:52:47.069 --> 00:52:49.903
and exit the vaults. before the backup power comes on.

799
00:52:49.931 --> 00:52:51.665
Camponotus pennsylvanicus.

800
00:52:51.807 --> 00:52:54.340
Alternatively known as a carpenter ant.

801
00:52:54.436 --> 00:52:56.769
Ideal for ground and air transport.

802
00:52:57.179 --> 00:52:59.246
Wait a minute. I know this guy.

803
00:52:59.436 --> 00:53:01.370
I'm going to call him Antony.

804
00:53:02.221 --> 00:53:03.554
That's good. that's. that's very good

805
00:53:03.601 --> 00:53:04.734
because this time

806
00:53:05.173 --> 00:53:08.373
you're really going to have
to learn how to control him.

807
00:53:08.437 --> 00:53:11.170
Tell them to put the sugar in the teacup.

808
00:53:14.124 --> 00:53:15.257
Oh. you okay Dr.-

809
00:53:22.616 --> 00:53:23.616
Ah!

810
00:53:24.481 --> 00:53:25.481
Ah!!

811
00:53:26.788 --> 00:53:29.021
Hank wants you outside
for target practice.

812
00:53:29.080 --> 00:53:31.680
The suit has no weapons
so I made you these discs.

813
00:53:31.745 --> 00:53:32.745
Red shrinks.

814
00:53:34.032 --> 00:53:35.032
Blue enlarges.

815
00:53:37.805 --> 00:53:39.405
Solenopsis mandibularis.

816
00:53:39.640 --> 00:53:44.106
Known for their bite. the fire ants
have evolved into remarkable architects.

817
00:53:44.151 --> 00:53:47.551
They are handy to get you
in and out of difficult places.

818
00:53:56.875 --> 00:53:58.809
You can do it Scott. come on.

819
00:54:01.875 --> 00:54:03.342
They're not listening to me.

820
00:54:03.389 --> 00:54:05.456
You have to commit.
you have to mean it.

821
00:54:06.458 --> 00:54:07.925
No shortcuts. no lies.

822
00:54:09.090 --> 00:54:13.123
Throwing insults into the mix will not
do anyone any good. Hope.

823
00:54:13.179 --> 00:54:14.612
We don't have time for coddling.

824
00:54:14.673 --> 00:54:17.040
Our focus should be on helping Scott.

825
00:54:17.087 --> 00:54:18.654
Really?

826
00:54:19.234 --> 00:54:21.501
Is that where our focus should be?

827
00:54:45.196 --> 00:54:46.196
Hope!

828
00:54:55.324 --> 00:54:57.924
I don't know why I came
to you in the first place.

829
00:55:06.844 --> 00:55:08.777
We can't do this without her.

830
00:55:13.566 --> 00:55:14.566
Oh God.

831
00:55:14.611 --> 00:55:16.344
You gotta lock your doors.

832
00:55:16.618 --> 00:55:17.517
I mean. really.

833
00:55:17.566 --> 00:55:19.699
There's some weird folks
in this neighborhood.

834
00:55:19.778 --> 00:55:21.645
Do you think this is a joke?

835
00:55:22.365 --> 00:55:24.865
Do you have any idea what
he's asking you to risk?

836
00:55:24.913 --> 00:55:27.146
- You have a daughter.
- I'm doing this for her.

837
00:55:27.238 --> 00:55:30.038
You know when my mother died
I didn't see him for two weeks?

838
00:55:30.881 --> 00:55:31.948
He was in grief.

839
00:55:32.118 --> 00:55:33.651
Yeah. so was I. and I was seven.

840
00:55:33.702 --> 00:55:36.335
And he never came back. not
in any way that counted.

841
00:55:37.014 --> 00:55:39.614
He just sent me off to boarding school.

842
00:55:40.621 --> 00:55:41.955
You know. I thought.

843
00:55:42.000 --> 00:55:44.867
with all that's at stake.
just maybe we might

844
00:55:44.894 --> 00:55:46.894
have a chance at making peace.

845
00:55:46.900 --> 00:55:49.133
But even now he still
wants to shut me out.

846
00:55:49.170 --> 00:55:50.903
He doesn't want to shut you out.

847
00:55:50.987 --> 00:55:52.787
- He trusts you.
- Then why are you here?

848
00:55:53.789 --> 00:55:54.789
It proves that he loves you.

849
00:55:57.059 --> 00:55:58.792
Hope. Look at me.

850
00:56:00.147 --> 00:56:01.147
I'm expendable.

851
00:56:02.630 --> 00:56:03.963
That's why I'm here.

852
00:56:05.327 --> 00:56:07.527
You must've realized that by now.

853
00:56:07.868 --> 00:56:11.268
I mean. that's why I'm
in the suit and you're not.

854
00:56:12.067 --> 00:56:14.934
He'd rather lose than fight
than lose you.

855
00:56:16.406 --> 00:56:17.406
Anyway.

856
00:56:18.773 --> 00:56:23.707
You know. I didn't know you had a
daughter when I called the cops on you.

857
00:56:28.238 --> 00:56:29.305
What's her name?

858
00:56:30.092 --> 00:56:31.092
Cassie.

859
00:56:32.436 --> 00:56:33.703
It's a pretty name.

860
00:56:37.312 --> 00:56:38.345
You have to clear your mind. Scott.

861
00:56:38.392 --> 00:56:40.992
You have to make your thoughts precise.
that's how it works.

862
00:56:43.421 --> 00:56:44.688
Think about Cassie.

863
00:56:44.977 --> 00:56:48.977
about how badly you want to see her.
and use that to focus.

864
00:56:57.424 --> 00:57:01.824
Open your eyes and just think
about what you want the ants to do.

865
00:57:24.805 --> 00:57:25.805
Good.

866
00:57:43.970 --> 00:57:49.370
Your mother convinced me to let
her join me on my missions.

867
00:57:49.874 --> 00:57:51.841
They called her the Wasp.

868
00:57:52.707 --> 00:57:54.274
She was born to it.

869
00:57:56.353 --> 00:58:02.153
And there's not a day that goes by
that I don't regret having said yes.

870
00:58:06.859 --> 00:58:07.859
It was 1987.

871
00:58:09.410 --> 00:58:13.210
Separatists had hijacked a
Soviet missile silo in Kursk

872
00:58:15.246 --> 00:58:18.046
and launched an ICBM at the United States.

873
00:58:25.750 --> 00:58:28.283
The only way to the internal mechanics

874
00:58:28.842 --> 00:58:30.642
was through solid titanium.

875
00:58:39.701 --> 00:58:44.234
I knew I had to shrink between the
molecules to disarm the missile.

876
00:58:44.615 --> 00:58:48.515
but my regulator had sustained
too much damage.

877
00:58:50.140 --> 00:58:52.339
Your mother. she didn't hesitate.

878
00:58:55.127 --> 00:58:56.127
Janet! No!

879
00:59:03.317 --> 00:59:05.183
She turned off her regulator

880
00:59:06.505 --> 00:59:08.638
and went sub-atomic

881
00:59:09.841 --> 00:59:11.374
to deactivate the bomb.

882
00:59:13.725 --> 00:59:15.024
She was gone.

883
00:59:19.747 --> 00:59:21.647
Your mom died a hero.

884
00:59:23.787 --> 00:59:28.920
And I spent the next ten years
trying to learn all I could

885
00:59:29.467 --> 00:59:31.267
about the quantum realm.

886
00:59:35.420 --> 00:59:37.687
You were trying to bring her back.

887
00:59:38.765 --> 00:59:41.765
But all I learned
was we know nothing.

888
00:59:47.327 --> 00:59:48.660
It's not your fault.

889
00:59:51.122 --> 00:59:52.655
She made her choice.

890
00:59:58.110 --> 01:00:00.443
But why didn't you tell me this sooner?

891
01:00:02.137 --> 01:00:04.903
I was trying to protect you.

892
01:00:06.848 --> 01:00:08.115
I lost your mother.

893
01:00:10.474 --> 01:00:13.174
I didn't mean to lose you too.

894
01:00:14.364 --> 01:00:15.364
I'm sorry.

895
01:00:18.657 --> 01:00:19.724
This is awesome.

896
01:00:21.519 --> 01:00:23.119
It's awesome. Y'know.

897
01:00:23.398 --> 01:00:25.897
You guys are breaking down walls.
you're healing.

898
01:00:26.274 --> 01:00:27.274
It's important.

899
01:00:30.921 --> 01:00:32.054
I ruined the moment didn't I.

900
01:00:32.078 --> 01:00:33.278
Yes. you did. yes.

901
01:00:35.096 --> 01:00:36.896
I'm going to make some tea.

902
01:00:42.555 --> 01:00:43.555
Nailed it!

903
01:00:52.945 --> 01:00:54.678
That's a good boy. Antony.

904
01:01:24.223 --> 01:01:27.556
The final phase of your training
will be a stealth incursion.

905
01:01:27.629 --> 01:01:28.596
It's freezing!

906
01:01:28.601 --> 01:01:31.401
You couldn't make a simple flannel lining?

907
01:01:31.690 --> 01:01:35.090
We must retrieve this prototype
of a signal decoy.

908
01:01:35.094 --> 01:01:37.893
it's a device that I invented
from my SHIELD days.

909
01:01:37.895 --> 01:01:42.662
We need it to counteract the transmission blockers
that Cross installed in the Futures vault.

910
01:01:42.757 --> 01:01:46.424
It's currently collecting dust in one of
Howard Stark's old storage facilities

911
01:01:46.443 --> 01:01:47.776
in upstate New York.

912
01:01:48.009 --> 01:01:50.042
Should be a piece of cake.

913
01:01:50.179 --> 01:01:51.646
You're over the target area.

914
01:01:51.705 --> 01:01:53.872
Disengage. now. Scott.

915
01:01:54.345 --> 01:01:55.345
Squadron A. go.

916
01:01:55.983 --> 01:01:56.983
B. go.

917
01:01:58.989 --> 01:01:59.989
C. go.

918
01:02:01.494 --> 01:02:03.694
All right. Antony. please
don't drop me this time.

919
01:02:04.892 --> 01:02:07.025
Ah. it feels like a big leap
from sugar cubes to this.

920
01:02:07.518 --> 01:02:08.518
Stay calm.

921
01:02:10.977 --> 01:02:12.910
Uh. guys. we might
have a problem.

922
01:02:12.978 --> 01:02:16.111
Hank. didn't you say this
was some old warehouse?

923
01:02:16.294 --> 01:02:17.294
It's not!

924
01:02:18.462 --> 01:02:19.729
You son of a bitch!

925
01:02:22.943 --> 01:02:23.576
Scott. get out of there.

926
01:02:23.614 --> 01:02:25.246
Abort! Abort now.

927
01:02:26.070 --> 01:02:28.870
No. it's okay. It doesn't
look like anyone's home.

928
01:02:28.942 --> 01:02:30.742
Antony. get me to the roof.

929
01:02:31.457 --> 01:02:32.924
He's gonna lose the suit.

930
01:02:32.944 --> 01:02:34.611
He's gonna lose his life.

931
01:02:40.126 --> 01:02:43.460
All right I'm on the roof
of the target building.

932
01:02:43.685 --> 01:02:44.718
Somebody's home. Scott.

933
01:02:48.512 --> 01:02:49.345
What's going on down there. Sam?

934
01:02:49.367 --> 01:02:50.567
It's the Falcon!

935
01:02:51.203 --> 01:02:54.169
I had a sensor trip but
I'm not seeing anything.

936
01:02:54.235 --> 01:02:54.935
Wait a second.

937
01:02:55.029 --> 01:02:56.562
Abort Scott. abort now.

938
01:02:57.085 --> 01:02:58.652
It's okay.
He can't see me.

939
01:02:58.778 --> 01:02:59.778
I can see you.

940
01:02:59.886 --> 01:03:00.886
He can see me.

941
01:03:03.247 --> 01:03:04.847
Hi. I'm Scott.

942
01:03:05.313 --> 01:03:06.680
Did he just say "Hi I'm Scott?"

943
01:03:06.775 --> 01:03:07.875
What are you doing here?

944
01:03:07.905 --> 01:03:08.805
First off.

945
01:03:09.044 --> 01:03:10.144
I'm a big fan.

946
01:03:10.182 --> 01:03:12.714
'Preciate it. So who the hell are you?

947
01:03:13.046 --> 01:03:14.046
I'm Ant-Man.

948
01:03:14.337 --> 01:03:15.337
Ant-Man?

949
01:03:15.594 --> 01:03:17.594
What. you haven't heard of me?

950
01:03:17.835 --> 01:03:20.168
Nah. you wouldn't have heard of me.

951
01:03:20.269 --> 01:03:21.336
You want to tell me what you want?

952
01:03:21.401 --> 01:03:23.901
I was hoping I could grab a
piece of technology

953
01:03:23.941 --> 01:03:25.574
just for a few days. and return it.

954
01:03:25.611 --> 01:03:28.311
I need it to save the world.
You know how that is.

955
01:03:28.385 --> 01:03:30.085
I know exactly how that is.

956
01:03:30.138 --> 01:03:32.305
Located the breach.
Bringing him in.

957
01:03:32.310 --> 01:03:33.443
Sorry about this.

958
01:03:37.351 --> 01:03:39.218
What the hell are you doing?

959
01:03:42.062 --> 01:03:46.129
Breach is an adult male who
has some sort of shrinking tech.

960
01:03:59.843 --> 01:04:01.443
Sorry about that. sorry.

961
01:04:01.744 --> 01:04:02.744
That's enough!

962
01:04:25.637 --> 01:04:27.104
Antony. a little help.

963
01:04:39.871 --> 01:04:41.004
I've lost visual.

964
01:04:50.273 --> 01:04:51.606
He's inside my pack.

965
01:04:51.659 --> 01:04:52.659
Sorry.

966
01:04:54.314 --> 01:04:56.514
You seem like a really great guy.

967
01:05:20.591 --> 01:05:24.924
It's really important to me that
Cap never finds out about this.

968
01:05:27.536 --> 01:05:30.803
That was completely irresponsible
and dangerous.

969
01:05:31.471 --> 01:05:33.870
You jeopardized everything.

970
01:05:49.917 --> 01:05:50.917
You got it.

971
01:05:54.961 --> 01:05:55.961
Well done.

972
01:05:56.042 --> 01:05:56.742
Wait a minute.

973
01:05:56.775 --> 01:05:58.474
Did you just compliment me?

974
01:05:58.540 --> 01:05:59.340
He did. didn't he?

975
01:05:59.367 --> 01:06:01.100
Kinda sounded like he did.

976
01:06:02.913 --> 01:06:04.313
I was good. wasn't I?

977
01:06:05.941 --> 01:06:09.241
Hey. how about the fact that I
fought an Avenger. and didn't die?

978
01:06:09.241 --> 01:06:11.374
Now let's not dwell on the past.

979
01:06:11.731 --> 01:06:13.664
We gotta finish our planning.

980
01:06:16.287 --> 01:06:17.287
Don't mind him.

981
01:06:18.408 --> 01:06:19.408
You did good.

982
01:06:27.087 --> 01:06:28.087
Darren!

983
01:06:30.741 --> 01:06:32.807
How the hell'd you get in here?

984
01:06:33.364 --> 01:06:35.697
You left the front door open. Hank.

985
01:06:36.131 --> 01:06:37.865
It's official. You're old.

986
01:06:38.915 --> 01:06:39.915
The plans!

987
01:06:41.462 --> 01:06:42.596
He will kill him.

988
01:06:46.526 --> 01:06:48.926
Well to what do I owe this pleasure?

989
01:06:50.323 --> 01:06:51.457
I have good news.

990
01:06:51.644 --> 01:06:52.644
Really?

991
01:06:53.556 --> 01:06:54.556
What's that?

992
01:06:55.551 --> 01:06:56.551
Pym Tech.

993
01:06:57.537 --> 01:06:59.137
the company you created.

994
01:06:59.927 --> 01:07:04.160
is about to become one of the most
profitable operations in the world.

995
01:07:04.215 --> 01:07:07.882
We're anticipating 15 billion
in sales tomorrow alone.

996
01:07:14.852 --> 01:07:15.852
You're welcome.

997
01:07:20.106 --> 01:07:23.239
I know this is odd. but
I'd like you to be there.

998
01:07:23.299 --> 01:07:26.032
This is my moment.
I want you to see it.

999
01:07:26.256 --> 01:07:27.822
Sure. Darren. Yeah. sure.

1000
01:07:27.907 --> 01:07:28.907
I'll be there.

1001
01:07:46.328 --> 01:07:47.861
What did you see in me?

1002
01:07:48.650 --> 01:07:50.450
I don't know what you mean.

1003
01:07:51.289 --> 01:07:53.689
All those years ago.
you picked me.

1004
01:07:54.062 --> 01:07:55.196
What did you see?

1005
01:07:57.820 --> 01:07:58.820
I saw myself.

1006
01:07:59.657 --> 01:08:01.657
Then why did you push me away?

1007
01:08:03.935 --> 01:08:06.135
Because I saw too much of myself.

1008
01:08:18.037 --> 01:08:21.236
He knows. he's baiting you.
We have to call it off.

1009
01:08:21.335 --> 01:08:22.569
We're all taking risks.

1010
01:08:22.635 --> 01:08:23.868
What if he saw me here?

1011
01:08:23.952 --> 01:08:25.185
He didn't. There's no way.

1012
01:08:25.240 --> 01:08:26.640
How do you know that?

1013
01:08:34.680 --> 01:08:35.680
Darren. hi.

1014
01:08:36.562 --> 01:08:37.562
Hope.

1015
01:08:37.792 --> 01:08:39.392
Where are you right now?

1016
01:08:40.054 --> 01:08:41.187
I'm at home. why?

1017
01:08:41.500 --> 01:08:42.567
I just saw Hank.

1018
01:08:42.804 --> 01:08:45.070
I still get nothing but
contempt from him.

1019
01:08:45.112 --> 01:08:48.345
Don't let him rile you up. he's just...
he's a senile old man.

1020
01:08:48.582 --> 01:08:50.949
We need to start everyone
working around the clock.

1021
01:08:50.963 --> 01:08:53.030
get the assembly line up and running.

1022
01:08:53.075 --> 01:08:54.608
And I'm tripling security.

1023
01:08:54.708 --> 01:08:59.941
Full sensors at all entrances. and
exterior air vents fitted with steel micro mesh.

1024
01:09:00.000 --> 01:09:01.000
Great. Good idea.

1025
01:09:01.525 --> 01:09:02.525
Thank you. hope.

1026
01:09:02.774 --> 01:09:05.174
I'm so lucky to have you on my team.

1027
01:09:08.664 --> 01:09:11.330
He's tripling security. he's lost his mind.

1028
01:09:11.395 --> 01:09:12.662
and he's on to you.

1029
